*colordiff-1.0.5-r2 (11 Jul 2005)

  11 Jul 2005; Aron Griffis <agriffis@gentoo.org>
  -colordiff-1.0.5-r1.ebuild, +colordiff-1.0.5-r2.ebuild:
  Version 1.0.5 removes the --no-banner option, so make the default in
  /etc/colordiffrc be banner=no

  11 Jul 2005; Gustavo Zacarias <gustavoz@gentoo.org>
  colordiff-1.0.5.ebuild:
  Stable on sparc

*colordiff-1.0.5-r1 (11 Jul 2005)

  11 Jul 2005; Aron Griffis <agriffis@gentoo.org> colordiff-1.0.5.ebuild,
  +colordiff-1.0.5-r1.ebuild:
  Mark 1.0.5 stable on alpha amd64 x86. Update to -r1 with a minor config file
  fix: use the default foreground color for plain instead of white or black.
  Should be able to mark -r1 stable in a matter of days if it doesn't blow up
  for anybody...

  08 May 2005; Aron Griffis <agriffis@gentoo.org> colordiff-1.0.5.ebuild:
  stable on ia64

  04 Apr 2005; Aron Griffis <agriffis@gentoo.org> colordiff-1.0.4.ebuild:
  stable on amd64

